				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: macros<a name="7685"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 29 03 7:35 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I tried that at one time but the appropriate command is /pause xx with xx being the appropriate delay.  I used between 28-30 which equals about 3 seconds depending on lag.  Speaking of lag that is the big drawback to using this command.  If you are getting to much lag the pause will not take fully and the next song won't cast for you.  Missed notes will also play havoc with these type of macros.  I only use the /pause command for non-twisting keys like my assist key.  I use /target MA on first line /pause 5 or so on second line then /assist on line 3.  I also have mez key set with /cast 7 (my mez song loc) on line 1, /pause 5 on line 2 and on last line /attack off.  If you do want to use the /pause command you can put it on the same line as one other command.  For example /cast 1, /pause 30 but you must have the pause second, don't ask me why, but it works.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
