				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: macros<a name="8138"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 13 03 12:11 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The Pause has to be on the same line as the cast and must be listed first.  If you don't know how to use it, most things like this are explained in the everquest supplemental document in the EQ directory.  The best hotkey setups that I use are as follows:
<br />

<br />
/stopsong
<br />
/pause 1, /cast 1
<br />

<br />
I only use 1 song per social since there are so many missed notes now at higher levels.  This allows for a 4 song twist and allows for an instant reattempt to cast if you miss the note.  Having the 2 songs in a given social means that if you miss the note for either song, you have a minimum of 3 seconds that you cannot use a song and that can be painful.  You miss notes on both songs, you are likely dead.
<br />

<br />
One song per social like I showed allows for there to only be a 1/10th of a second lost time if you miss the note.  This is especially good on raids where the graphical lag is so bad from numbers of players that you have to use the keyboard for each song.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
